SIMPLE: migrate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Migrate
<hw>Mi"grate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Migrated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Migrating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>migratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>migrare</ets> to migrate,
transfer.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To remove from one country or region to another,
with a view to residence; to change one's place of residence; to remove;
<as>as, the Moors who <ex>migrated</ex> from Africa into Spain; to
<ex>migrate</ex> to the West.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass periodically from one region or climate to
another for feeding or breeding; -- said of certain birds, fishes, and
quadrupeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Migration</ent>⟦br⟧
